s important criteria for determining the best interest of the child and concludes that the role of law in the lives of children must be to preserve their connections with those that love them.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Aug 2021) 0aChild supportxLaw and legislationzCanada. 0aChildren of divorced parentszCanada. 0aCustody of childrenzCanada. 0aDivorcexLaw and legislationzCanada. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Children's Studies.2bisacsh40uhttps://doi.org/10.3138/978144269773740uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781442697737423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781442697737.jpg  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_SN  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_SN  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aEBA_STMALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA12STME  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK